---
import Container from "@/components/container.astro";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  description="EdgeEver Web Clipper privacy policy covering webpage content, URLs, API tokens, and locally stored settings."
>
  <Container>
    <main class="mx-auto max-w-3xl py-12 text-slate-700 md:py-20">
      <article class="rounded-lg border border-slate-200 bg-white p-8 shadow-sm md:p-10">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-slate-950">EdgeEver Web Clipper Privacy Policy</h1>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm text-slate-500">Effective: July 17, 2026</p>

        <div class="mt-8 space-y-8 leading-7">
          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Single purpose</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">EdgeEver Web Clipper only converts the current webpage or selected content that the user explicitly chooses to save into Markdown and sends it to the user's configured EdgeEver instance.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Data handled</h2>
            <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li>EdgeEver instance URL, API token, and default notebook ID are stored in Chrome's local extension storage so the extension can connect to the instance chosen by the user.</li>
              <li>The current page title and URL, plus selected content or the article body extracted from the page, are processed only after the user clicks “Save current page.”</li>
              <li>The capture time is added to the saved note for source traceability.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Use and transmission</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">Page content is extracted and converted to Markdown locally in the browser, then sent directly over the network to the EdgeEver instance configured by the user. The extension developer operates no relay service and does not receive, store, or view the content, URLs, or API token.</p>
            <p class="mt-3">The extension includes no advertising, analytics, tracking, or telemetry. Data is not sold or shared with advertising platforms, data brokers, or other third parties.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Permission use</h2>
            <ul class="mt-3 list-disc space-y-2 pl-6">
              <li><strong>activeTab</strong>: accesses the current tab only after the user invokes the extension to save it.</li>
              <li><strong>scripting</strong>: runs the content extraction script in the current page.</li>
              <li><strong>storage</strong>: stores the instance URL, API token, and default notebook settings locally.</li>
              <li><strong>Optional host permissions</strong>: grants network access only to the EdgeEver instance configured by the user.</li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Security and retention</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">Users should use an HTTPS EdgeEver instance and protect their API token. Extension settings remain in local Chrome extension storage until the user changes them, clears extension data, or uninstalls the extension. Clipped content is retained by the user's own EdgeEver instance and can be edited or deleted there.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Chrome Web Store Limited Use</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">Information received from Chrome APIs is used only to provide the user-facing web clipping feature described above. Its use complies with the Chrome Web Store User Data Policy, including the Limited Use requirements.</p>
          </section>

          <section>
            <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Contact</h2>
            <p class="mt-3">For questions about this policy or the extension's data practices, contact the project maintainers through <a class="text-teal-700 underline" href="https://github.com/tianma-if/edgeever/issues" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub Issues</a>.</p>
          </section>
        </div>
      </article>
    </main>
  </Container>
</Layout>
